Notifications

Old

  • RT-PCR test requirement for Brazilians and foreigners to enter Brazil

    Are you traveling to the US or Europe? Please have in mind the new rules for entry into Brazil in accordance with Ordinance No. 630 of 17/12/2020 issued by the Civil Cabinet:

    1) As of December 30, 2020 , the entry of foreign customers and Brazilians over the age of 12 is only authorized upon presentation at check-in of the RT-PCR method test showing a non-reactive (negative) /result for COVID-19. . The RT-PCR test must be collected no later than 72 hours before departure.

    2) In addition to submitting the RT-PCR type test, all customers must complete the Traveler's Health Declaration (DSV) according to the guidelines in the link that will be made available at the Anvisa portal.

    Thank you,

    Azul Team
